components.name: AutoRefreshComponent

propertiesClass.name: timer$
propertiesClass.defaultValue:
timer(0, 1000)
    .pipe(
      map((seconds) => this.period - seconds - 1),
      take(this.period),
      delayWhen(() => of(this.refreshing)),
      finalize(() => this.refresh.emit()),
      repeat(),
    )

components.templateData:
<clr-toggle-container>
  <clr-toggle-wrapper>
    <input
      type="checkbox"
      clrToggle
      [formControl]="toggleControl"
      (change)="onToggle()"
    >
    <label class="p5 text-label">
      <ng-container *ngIf="!toggleControl.value; else timer">
        Auto refresh disabled
      </ng-container>

      <ng-template #timer>
        <ng-container *ngIf="!refreshing && timer$ | async as timer; else refresh">
          Auto refresh in {{ timer }} sec
        </ng-container>

        <ng-template #refresh>
          Refreshing...
        </ng-template>
      </ng-template>
    </label>
  </clr-toggle-wrapper>
</clr-toggle-container>

components.name: PartialStringFilterComponent
components.templateData:
<form [formGroup]="form">
  <input
    type="text"
    autocomplete="off"
    placeholder="{{ placeholder }}"
    clrInput
    formControlName="input"
    #input
  />
  <clr-control-helper *ngIf="isToShort">
    Please provide at least {{ characterLimit }} characters
  </clr-control-helper>
  <clr-control-helper *ngIf="!isToShort">
    Searching '{{ propertyDisplayName }}' by partial match
  </clr-control-helper>
  <button
    type="button"
    class="btn btn-icon btn-block btn-sm"
    (click)="reset()"
    [disabled]="!isDirty"
  >
    <clr-icon shape="refresh"></clr-icon>
    RESET
  </button>
</form>
